Gov. Aminu Masari of Katsina State, has signed an Executive Order towards tacking Security Challenges in the state. Malam Yahaya Sirika, the state’s Commissioner for Information and Culture, said this in a statement on Friday in Katsina, saying that the order was in exercise of the powers conferred on the governor by Section 176(2) of the1999 Constitution. Sirika said the order which took effect from Jan. 1 banned all forms of political thuggery and associated crimes in the state.   Abdulrazaq sets up committee to probe violence over hijab     There is need to transform Africa into knowledge-based…     ‘Indaboski! If only for 2nd Niger Bridge, this country…   He said that indiscriminate posting of political parties posters and banners in roundabouts, government buildings as well as offices and public places were also banned. - Advertisement - “Gathering and movement of political thugs known as Bacha, Kauraye under any other name or guise to intimidate, harass and maim the innocent populace are also totally banned. “Any person or group that contravenes the provisions will be charged for an offence punishable under Section 114 of the penal code law,” Sirika said.   (NAN) SPONSORED